==English==
===Etymology===
From [[under]] + [[crank]]; dating from a time when movie film was advanced in a camera by the turning of a crank.

===Noun===
{{en-verb}}

#{{cattag|Filmology}} To [[shoot]] a [[scene]] while advancing the [[film]] in the [[camera]] more slowly than it will on [[screen]].  This results in [[speeding]] up the action in the final film.

